Date: Thu, 27 Apr 2017 19:02:25 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] drm/i915: Remove hdmi_connected from LPE audio pdata
Mime-version: 1.0
Content-type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-transfer-encoding: 8bit
Git-commit: 265fa2e18f50cc55c0d0517b29bd5cdd5b4f776f
Patch-mainline: v4.13-rc1
References: FATE#322643 bsc#1055900

We can determine that the pipe was shut down from pipe<0, so there's
no point in duplicating that information as 'hdmi_connected'.

V2: Use pipe<0 instead of port<0 as we'll want to do per-port    PCM devices later    Initialize pipe to -1 to inidicate inactive initial state

